701826f-a.title: Bronx: Southern Boulevard - 143rd Street (East)
701826f-a.text:
Southern Boulevard, north side, west from East 134th Street to
(No. 65) its junction with East 133rd Street, showing the cleared area
created by the demolition of buildings which formerly stood there. The
houses were razed to permit the construction of an approach to the Tri-
borough Bridge. In the center of the view are seen the rears of 2-story
houses on the south side of East 134th Street, and in the right back-
ground, buildings on the north side of East 135th Street.
July 29, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
